  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Empowering vulnerable young women</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project supports vulnerable and homeless girls and young women living in Kigali, Rwanda. Involvement in domestic or sex work means that vulnerable and homeless girls are often invisible to society and there is a lack of services and support for them. This project works with around 3,000 girls and young women aged 7-25 in the Kigali area. rYico provides access to a safe refuge house for girls in urgent need or in danger. Through a drop-in and a helpline they provide legal advice and support individuals to make legal representation if necessary. They provide urgent medication and support them to access the correct treatment, and give advice on sexual health. They also work closely with community organisations, government bodies and other service providers to lobby for regulations to protect this vulnerable group, and raise awareness of their needs.</narrative>
  </description>
